            "text": "Mullica Township is a quiet, rural community nestled in the Pine Barrens of western Atlantic County. Known for its wooded surroundings, open space, and small-town charm, it appeals to buyers who value privacy, land, and a slower pace of life. Homes range from modest single-family houses to larger properties with acreage, often at more affordable prices than suburban or shore towns. Its location provides a balance of peaceful living while still being within a short drive to Hammonton, Egg Harbor City, and shore destinations.",
