            "tag": "P",
            "text": "Lawnside is a small, culturally rich borough with deep historical roots. As one of the first self-governing African American communities north of the Mason-Dixon Line, it carries a legacy of pride, resilience, and community spirit. Today, it remains a close-knit town with a welcoming vibe and accessible location.",
