            "tag": "P",
            "text": "Carneys Point offers homebuyers a practical and affordable option in Salem County, with a strong location near I-295, the NJ Turnpike, and the Delaware Memorial Bridge. This makes it a great choice for commuters working in Wilmington, Philadelphia, or Central Jersey. The town features a variety of housing options—from well-maintained older homes to more modern developments—at price points that suit many budgets. With local schools, shopping centers, and recreational spaces nearby, Carneys Point is a convenient and comfortable place to live. Residents enjoy community amenities like the Carneys Point Recreation Complex, as well as access to the Salem River for kayaking and fishing. Whether you’re a first-time buyer, downsizing, or investing, Carneys Point delivers value, accessibility, and a laid-back lifestyle that’s becoming increasingly attractive to homebuyers across South Jersey.",
